
tools;


machinery;


personal property such as furniture, antiques, collectibles, jewelry, artwork, clothing, and other
personal effects.

Eligible assets for solvency determinations include:


savings, proven by the previous 12 month period of financial institution statements;


Guaranteed Investment Certificates (GICs), proven by financial institution statements;


Treasury bills, proven by financial institution statements;


bonds issued by the Government of Canada which are transferrable (Canada Savings Bonds are not
acceptable because they are not transferable), proven by bond certificates;


stocks, proven by stock certificates, where the principle investment is at least 12 months old;

